text: The Sykes-Leigh House, also known as Rosewood Manor is a historic mansion in Columbus, Mississippi, U.S.. It was built in 1838 for Richard Sykes, a planter. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since March 14, 1985. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Mississippi Category:Greek Revival houses in Mississippi Category:Houses completed in 1838 Category:National Register of Historic Places in Lowndes County, Mississippi Category:Antebellum architecture
